==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Montem
<hw>Mon"tem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ad
montem</ets> to the hillock. See <er>Mount</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A custom, formerly practiced by the scholars at Eton school,
England, of going every third year, on Whittuesday, to a hillock near
the Bath road, and exacting money from all passers-by, to support at the
university the senior scholar of the school.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Montero</ent>⟦br⟧
